The paper deals with scheduling wireless links and optimizing power assignment, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of conflict graphs and graph-theoretic results suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper presents approximation algorithms, which is a topic in algorithms (cs.AL).
